MoveCost MoveCost Enum

Definition

Namespace:
Assembly:
System.Fabric.dll

Describes the move cost of a replica.

Edit

In this Article

public enum MoveCostPublic Enum MoveCost

Remarks

When a new replica or service instance is created it will get a default value for move cost. This value will be selected based on the service:

Fields

High High

Specifies the move cost of a replica as High.
Low Low

Specifies the move cost of a replica as Low.
Medium Medium

Specifies the move cost of a replica as Medium.
Zero Zero

Specifies the move cost of a replica as Zero.
